[4] Ukraine
Date: Tue 6 Mar 2018
Source: 112 UA [edited]
https://112.international/society/about-6500-people-infected-with-measles-in-ukraine-in-2018-26311.html


About 6500 people were infected with measles in Ukraine since the beginning of 2018, Viktor Lyashko, the Deputy Director-General on Supervision over Infectious Diseases of the Public Health Centre of Ukraine's Healthcare Ministry, reported.

"As at 6 Mar 2018, 684 people, including 266 adults and 418 children, were sickened with measles during the 9th week of 2018, and it is 12% less than the previous week. Totally, 6484 cases of the measles were spotted since the beginning of 2018, 2226 adults and 4258 children," he noted.

According to Lyashko, 4421 people were hospitalized. Seven people died: 5 of them were children and 2 adults.

"Five people died in Odesa region, one in Ivano-Frankivsk region and one more in Zakarpattia region," he said.

Lyashko claimed that most people infected with the measles [were from] Ivano-Frankivsk region, with 1426 people, and Zakarpattia region, with 1138 people. Kharkiv region had the least, with only 2 cases spotted.

Earlier, the European Health Security Agency reported that Ukraine was the 3rd in Europe with the number of people infected with measles in 2017. The leaders are Romania and Italy.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[There has been some discussion in the Ukraine press on whether the circulating genotype of measles is more virulent. "A dangerous genotype of the measles virus B3 (Kabul) is circulating in Odesa region, as stated in the Odesa Regional State Administration press release. People from the other regions of Ukraine are infected with European samples of the D8 virus. And only in Odesa region, in addition to the D3 genotype, the B3 (Kabul) is fixed. It is characterized by high pathogenicity and virulence. Its aggressiveness gives a high incidence and lethality. The results are approved by the special laboratory researches in Copenhagen," the report says. ... According to the latest data, 6 genotypes of measles are circulating in Ukraine. The genotype matters when we assess the situation from which country the strain was brought; we have measles strains brought from Singapore: D8, D4, D3. Genotypes were imported from Romania, Bulgaria, and Georgia, Demchyshyna said" (excerpted from https://112.international/article/measles-genotype-b3-kabul-found-in-odesa-region-is-this-type-the-deadliest-one-25521.html).

However, it really is lack of vaccination that is the problem. The measles genotype does not have an impact on the lethality or complications. The measles virus has a single serotype, although 23 genotypes have been identified by analysis of the sequences of the nucleoprotein (N) and hemagglutinin (H) genes. Infection by any genotype induces life-long immunity against all genotypes. No genotype has been associated with greater virulence or persistence. Some genotypes may be associated with specific geographic regions, although the majority cause outbreaks and sporadic cases in any country (excerpted from MM Mosquera et al. The Open Vaccine Journal, 2010, 3, 76-85 https://benthamopen.com/contents/pdf/TOVACJ/TOVACJ-3-76.pdf).

A HealthMap of Ukraine can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5672342,123. - Mod.LK]

